§ 107.73 Knowledge and training.
An initial aeronautical knowledge test and recurrent training covers the following areas of knowledge:
(a) Applicable regulations relating to small unmanned aircraft system rating privileges, limitations, and flight
operation;
(b) Airspace classification, operating requirements, and flight restrictions affecting small unmanned aircraft
operation;
